","og:image":"https://imagesvc.meredithcorp.io/v3/mm/image?q=85&c=sc&poi=face&w=1600&h=838&url=https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.onecms.io%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F28%2F2018%2F09%2Fstreet-style-collage-FNYPAK0716.jpg","og:image:width":"1600","og:image:height":"838","article:opinion":"false"} ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="cd[Schema.org]" [] ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="cd[JSON-LD]" [[{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@id":"https://www.travelandleisure.com/","name":"Home","image":null}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"@id":"https://www.travelandleisure.com/style","name":"Style","image":null}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"@id":"https://www.travelandleisure.com/style/travel-bags","name":"Travel Bags","image":null}}]},{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"17 Fanny Packs That Are Actually Cool","image":[{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://imagesvc.meredithcorp.io/v3/mm/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.onecms.io%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F28%2F2018%2F09%2Fcute-fanny-packs-FANNY0218.jpg","width":1600,"height":1000,"caption":"17 Fanny Packs That Are Actually Cool"}],"author":[{"@type":"Person","name":"Richelle Szypulski"}],"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Travel + Leisure","url":"https://www.travelandleisure.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.travelandleisure.com/img/logo.png","width":204,"height":60},"sameAs":["https://www.facebook.com/travelandleisure","https://twitter.com/TravelLeisure","https://www.pinterest.com/TravelLeisure/","https://www.instagram.com/travelandleisure/"]},"datePublished":"2018-09-28T14:57:13.000Z","dateModified":"2018-09-28T17:55:17.000Z","description":"Just when you think the fashion industry has done it all, it goes and reinvents the fanny pack. Sure, these next-generation, high style hip pouches are billed with sexier names — belt bags, waist wallets, bum bags — but we still see them for what they truly are.

The fanny pack has always been a statement piece, but until a few years ago that statement was either, “Hello, I am very obviously a tourist,” or, “Yes, ’80s-themed parties are still alive and well.” Buckling into one of these human-turned-kangaroo packs was not cute or trendy by any means.

Related:17 Cute Cross-body Bags No One Will Believe You Got on Amazon

Now, fanny packs are cinching waists and hanging low on the hips of runway models at Alexander Wang, Balenciaga, and Chloé shows. Fashion-forward celebrities Sarah Jessica Parker, Rihanna, and Blake Lively have been spotted toting their essentials waist-side. Sleek designer fanny packs are cropping up in many a street style shot.

And I’m finally coming to terms with the fact that I want one.

Through the lens of pure practicality, the fanny pack does no wrong. It’s easily accessible, hands-free, and the perfect size for when a backpack is too big and pockets too small. Wearing one, your upper body is totally unencumbered — a weight off your shoulders in every sense of the phrase. But how to style this former faux pas?

To keep it classic, stay simple. We love a minimalist leather fanny pack with a fitted white t-shirt, frayed denim, and some comfy travel shoes or around the waist of a casual, lightweight dress. For a bolder look, pair a printed pack with high-waisted shorts and a body suit or crop top. You can even belt one around a long wrap coat or cardigan to layer up when the temperature cools.

Join the revolution and take on your next music festival, day at the museum, or bike ride through the city with one of these 17 cute fanny packs by your side.","mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.travelandleisure.com/style/travel-bags/stylish-fanny-packs"}]] ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="sw" 800 ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="sh" 600 ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="v" 2.9.18 ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="r" stable ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="ec" 1 ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="o" 30 ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="fbp" fb.1.1591637815102.1988622930 ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="it" 1591637815001 ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="coo" false ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="es" automatic ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="tm" 3 ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW Content-Disposition: form-data; name="rqm" SB ------WebKitFormBoundarytzIwwARUZR7zcxcW--
